removed table and certain mentions of 1897 statistics as it misleadingly suggests the changes in demographics from 1897 to 1926 was due to the massacres/deportations between 1917-1921; however, there are many events that occurred in between (Armenian–Tatar massacres of 1905–1907, the Armenian Genocide, WWI, etc). No source has specifically mentioned these demographic changes in the context of the topic of this article so it's OR to use those statistics to suggesthat causal inference here.
